<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 11:54PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Roberts
and western Hemphill Counties through 1230 AM CDT...
At 1154 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Canadian, moving south at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Canadian and Lora.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
